OL,3,CStrictly dancer Amy Dowden made MBE
OL,4,Cfor raising awareness of bowel illness
OL,6,FIn January 2022 she was admitted to
OL,7,Fhospital in Manchester following a
OL,8,FCrohn's flare-up while on the Strictly
OL,9,Flive tour.
OL,11,FShe had previously suffered a flare-up
OL,12,Fin November 2021, shortly after the
OL,13,Ffilming of Strictly Come Dancing, when
OL,14,Fshe briefly moved in with her
OL,15,Fcelebrity partner, McFly star Tom
OL,16,FFletcher, and his wife Giovanna, while
OL,17,Fher husband was away.
OL,19,FCrohn's is described by the NHS as a
OL,20,Flifelong condition in which parts of
OL,21,Fthe digestive system become inflamed.
